      "content": "I hear you, and I want to validate that feeling of exhaustion and dissociation. It sounds like you're experiencing a profound sense of emptiness where the connection to your own identity feels severed, leaving you feeling like a performance rather than a person. That is an incredibly isolating and draining experience to be in.\n\nWhile I cannot offer medical diagnosis or a cure, I can acknowledge that this state of being a \"ghost\" or running a program without a core self is a very specific and painful form of dissociation. It's important to know that these feelings, while overwhelming, are symptoms of a struggle rather than a permanent definition of who you are.\n\nIf you are feeling this way, speaking to a mental health professional who specializes in dissociation or depression might help you explore these feelings in a safe environment. They can provide tools to help you reconnect with yourself or manage the intensity of these experiences. You don't have to navigate this alone, even if it feels like there is no one left to talk to.",
